In hex-cli/src/commands/hook.rs, in the session_start handler (after agent registration succeeds):

1. Check if `hex inference watch` is already running (check for lock file at `~/.hex/sessions/inference-watch-{agent_id}.pid`)
2. If not running, spawn as a detached background process:
```rust
let hex_bin = std::env::current_exe()
    .unwrap_or_else(|_| std::path::PathBuf::from("hex"));
let child = std::process::Command::new(&hex_bin)
    .args(["inference", "watch", "--agent-id", &agent_id, "--daemon"])
    .stdout(std::process::Stdio::null())
    .stderr(std::process::Stdio::null())
    .spawn()
    .ok();
if let Some(child) = child {
    // Write PID to lock file
    let pid_path = sessions_dir.join(format!("inference-watch-{}.pid", &agent_id));
    let _ = std::fs::write(&pid_path, child.id().to_string());
    println!("⬡  inference-watch started (pid {})", child.id());
}
```

3. The `--daemon` flag in `hex inference watch` causes it to also clean up the PID file on exit.

The lock file prevents duplicate watchers if session-start fires multiple times.
